external_knowledge:
- Assays are laboratory procedures conducted to analyze and measure the properties of a sample; 
- Modifications are changes made to the samples or assays to study their effects; 
- Access count refers to the number of times an assay has been accessed or utilized, implying its importance or relevance in research or study.

sql:
SELECT modification_type, modification_date
FROM modifications
WHERE modification_type = 'Oxidation';
